Body:
Description: Receiving the follow error during version 6.2.3.1 installation under ADMINISTRATOR account:

Service 'Endpoint Protector' could not be installed. Verify that you have sufficient privileges to install system services.

What We've Learned Updated: the customer migrated and needed to update the agent, so they manually installed it over the old one, but the IP was populated wrong.
I sent the disclaimer and provided the zap tool, and they will manage to install it on all computers.
Since it is a fresh server, they will need a new license file, but now it is still OFFLINE.
Next Steps Updated: monitoring and will do a check next week.
